description: a(n) is the n-th term in sequence A_n, respecting the offset.
comments: The sequence is undefined from n = 53 on, since A000053 has only 29 terms. Except for n = 47, n = 49 and n = 50, all terms up to there are known, cf. A091967. - _M. F. Hasler_, Sep 22 2013
links: E. M. Rains and N. J. A. Sloane, On Cayley's Enumeration of Alkanes (or 4-Valent Trees)., J. Integer Sequences, Vol. 2 (1999), Article 99.1.1.
N. J. A. Sloane, My favorite integer sequences, in Sequences and their Applications (Proceedings of SETA '98).
N. J. A. Sloane, Online Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences
maple: for m from 1 do  url:= sprintf("https://oeis.org/A%06d/b%06d.txt",m,m);  S:= URL:-Get(url);  L:= StringTools[Split](S,"\n");  for t in L do    g:= sscanf(t, "%d %d");    if nops(g) = 2 and g[1] = m then      a[m]:= g[2];      break    fi;  od;  if not assigned(a[m]) then break fi;od:seq(a[i],i=1..m-1); # _Robert Israel_, May 31 2015
crossrefs: See A091967, A107357, A102288 for other versions. See also A031214, A031135, A037181.
author: _Robert G. Wilson v_, Aug 23 2000
extensions: Rechecked and 4 more terms added by _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 25 2005
a(43) is presently unknown, since A000043(43) is the exponent of the 43rd Mersenne prime. a(44) = 668803781. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, May 25 2005
a(36) and a(42) corrected and a(43) to a(46) added by _Robert Israel_, May 31 2015
